WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.976 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.976 --> 00:00:03.416 align:middle line:90%
[CLASSICAL MUSIC]

00:00:03.416 --> 00:00:08.790 align:middle line:90%


00:00:08.790 --> 00:00:11.790 align:middle line:84%
>> My dad and my uncle had
founded Baskin-Robbins 31

00:00:11.790 --> 00:00:13.860 align:middle line:84%
Flavors, which became,
in my childhood,

00:00:13.860 --> 00:00:15.640 align:middle line:84%
the world's largest
ice cream company.

00:00:15.640 --> 00:00:19.188 align:middle line:84%
It was a
multibillion-dollar company.

00:00:19.188 --> 00:00:20.230 align:middle line:90%
I loved eating ice cream.

00:00:20.230 --> 00:00:21.760 align:middle line:90%
What kid doesn't?

00:00:21.760 --> 00:00:23.770 align:middle line:90%
And we had unlimited amounts.

00:00:23.770 --> 00:00:26.590 align:middle line:84%
We had an ice cream cone-shaped
swimming pool in our backyard.

00:00:26.590 --> 00:00:27.520 align:middle line:90%
I swam in it.

00:00:27.520 --> 00:00:31.220 align:middle line:84%
I had ice cream for
breakfast sometimes.

00:00:31.220 --> 00:00:32.119 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't well.

00:00:32.119 --> 00:00:33.000 align:middle line:90%
I was ill.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:33.830 align:middle line:90%
I was frail.

00:00:33.830 --> 00:00:38.950 align:middle line:10%
I actually had polio when I was
six, and I was in a wheelchair.

00:00:38.950 --> 00:00:43.250 align:middle line:10%
The doctor said I would be in a
wheelchair the rest of my life.

00:00:43.250 --> 00:00:45.920 align:middle line:10%


00:00:45.920 --> 00:00:49.180 align:middle line:10%
But then I started to regain
some feeling in my legs,

00:00:49.180 --> 00:00:52.120 align:middle line:10%
and some movement-- more on
the right leg than the left--

00:00:52.120 --> 00:00:53.770 align:middle line:10%
and I could kind of get around.

00:00:53.770 --> 00:00:57.000 align:middle line:90%


00:00:57.000 --> 00:00:59.790 align:middle line:84%
When I was 21, my left leg was
3 inches shorter than the right,

00:00:59.790 --> 00:01:01.290 align:middle line:84%
and I couldn't put
any weight on it.

00:01:01.290 --> 00:01:02.280 align:middle line:90%
It was very gimpy.

00:01:02.280 --> 00:01:05.400 align:middle line:84%
The doctor said, well, your
growing years are over now.

00:01:05.400 --> 00:01:07.062 align:middle line:84%
You're going to have
to live with this.

00:01:07.062 --> 00:01:08.562 align:middle line:10%
And I remember
thinking when I heard

00:01:08.562 --> 00:01:11.520 align:middle line:10%
that, I don't think you know
as much as you think you know.

00:01:11.520 --> 00:01:14.480 align:middle line:10%
I'm not accepting
that prognosis.

00:01:14.480 --> 00:01:18.990 align:middle line:84%
I'm an only son, so my dad
had groomed me to succeed him.

00:01:18.990 --> 00:01:20.550 align:middle line:90%
That was his plan.

00:01:20.550 --> 00:01:23.040 align:middle line:84%
And my dad was used to
getting what he wanted.

00:01:23.040 --> 00:01:23.840 align:middle line:90%
He was a doer.

00:01:23.840 --> 00:01:25.750 align:middle line:90%
He knew how to manifest stuff.

00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:27.060 align:middle line:90%
And he did.

00:01:27.060 --> 00:01:28.620 align:middle line:90%
He built this empire--

00:01:28.620 --> 00:01:29.640 align:middle line:90%
this ice cream empire.

00:01:29.640 --> 00:01:32.390 align:middle line:90%


00:01:32.390 --> 00:01:35.430 align:middle line:90%
He worked 80 hours a week.

00:01:35.430 --> 00:01:37.790 align:middle line:84%
And so I didn't really have
a relationship with him

00:01:37.790 --> 00:01:40.280 align:middle line:84%
much, other than
through the business.

00:01:40.280 --> 00:01:42.500 align:middle line:84%
But I started working
at Baskin-Robbins

00:01:42.500 --> 00:01:43.640 align:middle line:90%
when I was five years old.

00:01:43.640 --> 00:01:45.470 align:middle line:84%
I mean, all I did then
was sweep the floor,

00:01:45.470 --> 00:01:47.030 align:middle line:90%
empty the waste baskets.

00:01:47.030 --> 00:01:50.150 align:middle line:84%
But he wanted me to learn the
business from the inside out.

00:01:50.150 --> 00:01:55.200 align:middle line:84%
So as I got older, he would
give me age-appropriate jobs.

00:01:55.200 --> 00:01:57.750 align:middle line:84%
I worked in the factory where
ice cream was manufactured.

00:01:57.750 --> 00:02:00.110 align:middle line:84%
I worked in franchising,
where the stores were

00:02:00.110 --> 00:02:01.130 align:middle line:90%
located and sold.

00:02:01.130 --> 00:02:03.080 align:middle line:84%
I worked in advertising
and marketing.

00:02:03.080 --> 00:02:05.720 align:middle line:84%
I ran all the departments
of the business.

00:02:05.720 --> 00:02:08.210 align:middle line:84%
And that was my
relationship to my dad,

00:02:08.210 --> 00:02:11.780 align:middle line:84%
was we would drive together to
the office, then we drive home.

00:02:11.780 --> 00:02:13.190 align:middle line:90%
We talk about the business.

00:02:13.190 --> 00:02:15.418 align:middle line:84%
I hardly knew him
other than that,

00:02:15.418 --> 00:02:17.210 align:middle line:84%
because that's what
his life was all about.

00:02:17.210 --> 00:02:19.770 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
he wanted with me.

00:02:19.770 --> 00:02:24.080 align:middle line:10%
He didn't have much interest
in anything about my feelings

00:02:24.080 --> 00:02:28.820 align:middle line:10%
or thoughts other than, what did
I think about the next flavor?

00:02:28.820 --> 00:02:30.313 align:middle line:90%
And I actually liked it.

00:02:30.313 --> 00:02:31.730 align:middle line:84%
He was really good
at what he did.

00:02:31.730 --> 00:02:33.160 align:middle line:90%
He was really focused.

00:02:33.160 --> 00:02:35.660 align:middle line:84%
His ability to
concentrate was amazing.

00:02:35.660 --> 00:02:37.910 align:middle line:84%
Kind of yogic, in a
way, although not--

00:02:37.910 --> 00:02:40.640 align:middle line:84%
didn't have the values
of caring for others.

00:02:40.640 --> 00:02:43.160 align:middle line:84%
Although he wanted
to make people happy,

00:02:43.160 --> 00:02:45.260 align:middle line:90%
and he thought ice cream did.

00:02:45.260 --> 00:02:47.840 align:middle line:90%
I was a product of the '60s.

00:02:47.840 --> 00:02:50.810 align:middle line:84%
I had the opportunity to work
with Dr. Martin Luther King.

00:02:50.810 --> 00:02:52.020 align:middle line:10%
I marched with him.

00:02:52.020 --> 00:02:54.320 align:middle line:84%
I went to Alabama and
Mississippi to be with him

00:02:54.320 --> 00:02:56.295 align:middle line:84%
and participate in the
civil rights movement.

00:02:56.295 --> 00:02:57.420 align:middle line:90%
I was a kid from the north.

00:02:57.420 --> 00:02:58.520 align:middle line:90%
I was a white kid.

00:02:58.520 --> 00:03:01.520 align:middle line:84%
But to me, that was
history happening.

00:03:01.520 --> 00:03:05.300 align:middle line:84%
To me, that was an
opportunity to be

00:03:05.300 --> 00:03:08.900 align:middle line:84%
part of something--
to witness something

00:03:08.900 --> 00:03:11.690 align:middle line:84%
that was of immense
significance.

00:03:11.690 --> 00:03:16.570 align:middle line:84%
To me, the racism in our
society was abhorrent.

00:03:16.570 --> 00:03:19.132 align:middle line:84%
My dad thought, you're
trying to rock the boat.

00:03:19.132 --> 00:03:20.840 align:middle line:84%
They have their own
culture in the South.

00:03:20.840 --> 00:03:21.850 align:middle line:90%
You shouldn't go down there.

00:03:21.850 --> 00:03:23.110 align:middle line:90%
You should leave them alone.

00:03:23.110 --> 00:03:25.070 align:middle line:90%
They don't want you.

00:03:25.070 --> 00:03:27.250 align:middle line:84%
And then there was
the war in Vietnam,

00:03:27.250 --> 00:03:30.500 align:middle line:84%
and I thought it was a
ridiculously stupid idea--

00:03:30.500 --> 00:03:32.980 align:middle line:90%
the war-- and cruel.

00:03:32.980 --> 00:03:34.870 align:middle line:90%
And I opposed the war.

00:03:34.870 --> 00:03:36.850 align:middle line:90%
I protested it.

00:03:36.850 --> 00:03:39.290 align:middle line:90%
My dad was in favor of it.

00:03:39.290 --> 00:03:41.080 align:middle line:90%
So we had our differences.

00:03:41.080 --> 00:03:43.960 align:middle line:90%


00:03:43.960 --> 00:03:47.812 align:middle line:84%
And he was saying, well,
you could take stores

00:03:47.812 --> 00:03:49.270 align:middle line:84%
throughout the
world, and you could

00:03:49.270 --> 00:03:50.570 align:middle line:90%
build the company even bigger.

00:03:50.570 --> 00:03:53.290 align:middle line:90%
And I was thinking, yeah?

00:03:53.290 --> 00:03:55.270 align:middle line:90%
So what?

00:03:55.270 --> 00:03:58.150 align:middle line:90%
Why would I-- yes, I could.

00:03:58.150 --> 00:04:01.975 align:middle line:84%
You've built something
powerful, big, strong.

00:04:01.975 --> 00:04:04.122 align:middle line:90%
I could continue that.

00:04:04.122 --> 00:04:08.330 align:middle line:84%
But my uncle-- his
business partner,

00:04:08.330 --> 00:04:11.230 align:middle line:84%
my dad's brother-in-law--
died of a heart attack

00:04:11.230 --> 00:04:13.600 align:middle line:90%
at the age of 54.

00:04:13.600 --> 00:04:14.880 align:middle line:90%
He's a very big guy.

00:04:14.880 --> 00:04:17.050 align:middle line:90%
He ate a lot of ice cream.

00:04:17.050 --> 00:04:18.500 align:middle line:84%
And when he died,
I asked my dad,

00:04:18.500 --> 00:04:21.279 align:middle line:84%
do you think there could be a
connection between the amount

00:04:21.279 --> 00:04:26.080 align:middle line:84%
of ice cream that Burt Baskin
ate and his fatal heart attack?

00:04:26.080 --> 00:04:27.670 align:middle line:90%
And my dad said, no.

00:04:27.670 --> 00:04:29.860 align:middle line:84%
His ticker just got tired
and stopped working.

00:04:29.860 --> 00:04:32.260 align:middle line:84%
And then he looked at
me in a certain way.

00:04:32.260 --> 00:04:34.060 align:middle line:84%
And if I could
translate that look,

00:04:34.060 --> 00:04:39.080 align:middle line:84%
it said, don't ever
mention that again.

00:04:39.080 --> 00:04:41.770 align:middle line:84%
And I started to think
that my uncle's death

00:04:41.770 --> 00:04:44.680 align:middle line:84%
and some other things
that I saw, I was starting

00:04:44.680 --> 00:04:48.400 align:middle line:84%
to think, I don't think I want
to do what my dad has planned

00:04:48.400 --> 00:04:51.430 align:middle line:84%
for me, even though I was
enjoying working with him,

00:04:51.430 --> 00:04:55.653 align:middle line:84%
and the company was a
extravagant success,

00:04:55.653 --> 00:04:57.820 align:middle line:84%
and there was really unlimited
amounts of ice cream,

00:04:57.820 --> 00:05:01.990 align:middle line:84%
and almost unlimited amounts
of money, actually, coming in.

00:05:01.990 --> 00:05:04.060 align:middle line:90%
But I made a decision then.

00:05:04.060 --> 00:05:09.130 align:middle line:84%
And it was a decision that
defined my life ever since,

00:05:09.130 --> 00:05:13.485 align:middle line:84%
which was to walk away
from Baskin-Robbins

00:05:13.485 --> 00:05:15.610 align:middle line:84%
and the opportunity to run
the company with my dad,

00:05:15.610 --> 00:05:18.600 align:middle line:90%
and eventually, to inherit it.

00:05:18.600 --> 00:05:21.250 align:middle line:84%
And I also chose,
out of integrity,

00:05:21.250 --> 00:05:22.870 align:middle line:90%
to walk away from the money.

00:05:22.870 --> 00:05:26.320 align:middle line:84%
So I told my dad,
because I'm not

00:05:26.320 --> 00:05:29.230 align:middle line:84%
going to do what
you want me to do,

00:05:29.230 --> 00:05:30.610 align:middle line:84%
what you've planned
for me to do,

00:05:30.610 --> 00:05:34.960 align:middle line:84%
I think it's honorable and
respectful to you and to me

00:05:34.960 --> 00:05:38.140 align:middle line:84%
to not have any access
to your money, which

00:05:38.140 --> 00:05:40.420 align:middle line:90%
has come from the company.

00:05:40.420 --> 00:05:42.070 align:middle line:90%
My dad thought I was crazy.

00:05:42.070 --> 00:05:45.004 align:middle line:90%
[CLASSICAL MUSIC]

00:05:45.004 --> 00:05:51.850 align:middle line:90%


00:05:51.850 --> 00:05:54.295 align:middle line:90%
[LIGHT MUSIC]

00:05:54.295 --> 00:06:01.160 align:middle line:90%


00:06:01.160 --> 00:06:03.900 align:middle line:84%
>> I've met so many people that
have come to me 10 years, 15,

00:06:03.900 --> 00:06:05.143 align:middle line:90%
20 years--

00:06:05.143 --> 00:06:06.560 align:middle line:84%
arguably, you could
say-- too late

00:06:06.560 --> 00:06:09.440 align:middle line:84%
to discover that what
they've set out to achieve

00:06:09.440 --> 00:06:13.650 align:middle line:84%
wasn't really a part
of who they are.

00:06:13.650 --> 00:06:16.270 align:middle line:84%
Often, people are saying to
me, how do I find my passion?

00:06:16.270 --> 00:06:17.440 align:middle line:90%
How do I find my purpose?

00:06:17.440 --> 00:06:20.160 align:middle line:84%
Number one is we should reframe
the word "find" and say,

00:06:20.160 --> 00:06:21.053 align:middle line:90%
how do we uncover it?

00:06:21.053 --> 00:06:22.470 align:middle line:84%
Because finding
almost illustrates

00:06:22.470 --> 00:06:24.845 align:middle line:84%
that it's under the bed, or
it's over behind the counter,

00:06:24.845 --> 00:06:26.640 align:middle line:90%
or it's in a book somewhere.

00:06:26.640 --> 00:06:28.387 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately, it's
within ourselves.

00:06:28.387 --> 00:06:30.220 align:middle line:84%
So if you think about
that, and you say, OK,

00:06:30.220 --> 00:06:33.300 align:middle line:84%
what if I understand who I am,
therefore, what I am here to do

00:06:33.300 --> 00:06:37.407 align:middle line:84%
starts to become
very evident in time.

00:06:37.407 --> 00:06:39.240 align:middle line:84%
But if you want to
understand your patterns,

00:06:39.240 --> 00:06:41.050 align:middle line:84%
and you want to
understand self-sabotage,

00:06:41.050 --> 00:06:45.400 align:middle line:84%
you want to understand who
you are at the core, go back.

00:06:45.400 --> 00:06:48.355 align:middle line:84%
Go back and really do a
deep dive in your story.

00:06:48.355 --> 00:06:51.440 align:middle line:84%
It can be incredibly cathartic,
incredibly therapeutic.

00:06:51.440 --> 00:06:53.110 align:middle line:90%
It can be incredibly profound.

00:06:53.110 --> 00:06:57.010 align:middle line:84%
And what you'll find is insights
into what I call your gift.

00:06:57.010 --> 00:07:00.640 align:middle line:90%


00:07:00.640 --> 00:07:02.200 align:middle line:90%
Everyone has a gift.

00:07:02.200 --> 00:07:03.880 align:middle line:90%
People call it a purpose.

00:07:03.880 --> 00:07:05.530 align:middle line:90%
Some people call it a passion.

00:07:05.530 --> 00:07:07.690 align:middle line:84%
I believe we've all
got a gift within us.

00:07:07.690 --> 00:07:09.850 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't need to
be necessarily found.

00:07:09.850 --> 00:07:11.260 align:middle line:90%
It needs to be uncovered.

00:07:11.260 --> 00:07:12.820 align:middle line:90%
And the greatest clues--

00:07:12.820 --> 00:07:15.070 align:middle line:84%
I believe-- in terms
of what your gift is,

00:07:15.070 --> 00:07:16.930 align:middle line:84%
what you're here to
do, is in your story.

00:07:16.930 --> 00:07:19.700 align:middle line:90%


00:07:19.700 --> 00:07:22.520 align:middle line:84%
>> So many people that have
passed before us have been

00:07:22.520 --> 00:07:24.320 align:middle line:84%
generous enough
to give us wisdom.

00:07:24.320 --> 00:07:27.980 align:middle line:84%
One of my favorite books is by
Bronnie Ware, "The Five Regrets

00:07:27.980 --> 00:07:29.150 align:middle line:90%
of the Dying."

00:07:29.150 --> 00:07:33.650 align:middle line:84%
And the number one
regret that over hundreds

00:07:33.650 --> 00:07:38.150 align:middle line:84%
of beautiful souls that she's
helped pass to the other side,

00:07:38.150 --> 00:07:39.360 align:middle line:90%
it was this.

00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:44.720 align:middle line:84%
I wish I had lived a life true
to myself, and not the life

00:07:44.720 --> 00:07:47.280 align:middle line:90%
that others had expected of me.

00:07:47.280 --> 00:07:51.170 align:middle line:84%
And I feel like when it comes
to understanding that each of us

00:07:51.170 --> 00:07:54.620 align:middle line:84%
have a gift that we were put
on this Earth for a reason,

00:07:54.620 --> 00:07:58.400 align:middle line:84%
that there never will
be another one of us,

00:07:58.400 --> 00:08:02.420 align:middle line:84%
understanding that now is the
time to take whatever it is

00:08:02.420 --> 00:08:05.570 align:middle line:84%
that are our passions, and
our quirks, and our visions,

00:08:05.570 --> 00:08:07.220 align:middle line:84%
and bring them out
into the world,

00:08:07.220 --> 00:08:09.720 align:middle line:84%
because we will
never be here again.

00:08:09.720 --> 00:08:12.590 align:middle line:84%
And if we look at that
as something exciting,

00:08:12.590 --> 00:08:15.410 align:middle line:84%
that we have this
limited amount of time,

00:08:15.410 --> 00:08:19.190 align:middle line:84%
we're here to express our
joy, express our love, to make

00:08:19.190 --> 00:08:22.760 align:middle line:84%
a difference, to contribute
to others, all of a sudden,

00:08:22.760 --> 00:08:26.180 align:middle line:84%
it becomes less something
to fear and more

00:08:26.180 --> 00:08:30.998 align:middle line:84%
of something that's this
motivating, inspiring truth.

00:08:30.998 --> 00:08:33.740 align:middle line:90%
[SOMBER MUSIC]

00:08:33.740 --> 00:08:36.159 align:middle line:84%
What holds people back
is first and foremost

00:08:36.159 --> 00:08:38.650 align:middle line:90%
a desire for comfort and ease.

00:08:38.650 --> 00:08:39.450 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:08:39.450 --> 00:08:41.640 align:middle line:84%
They say, well, I
want to be great,

00:08:41.640 --> 00:08:43.720 align:middle line:90%
but I'm really comfortable here.

00:08:43.720 --> 00:08:45.600 align:middle line:90%
I understand this.

00:08:45.600 --> 00:08:48.690 align:middle line:84%
I'm not scared every
day, or I just--

00:08:48.690 --> 00:08:50.457 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to go
through that struggle.

00:08:50.457 --> 00:08:52.290 align:middle line:84%
I think the most important
thing in reaching

00:08:52.290 --> 00:08:56.010 align:middle line:84%
the next level in our life
is to honor the struggle.

00:08:56.010 --> 00:08:58.030 align:middle line:84%
That process is going
to bring hardship.

00:08:58.030 --> 00:08:59.520 align:middle line:90%
It's going to bring frustration.

00:08:59.520 --> 00:09:00.853 align:middle line:90%
It's going to bring the unknown.

00:09:00.853 --> 00:09:02.728 align:middle line:84%
It's going to bring
people making fun of you.

00:09:02.728 --> 00:09:05.300 align:middle line:84%
And instead of saying, oh, I'm
so scared of that, honor it.

00:09:05.300 --> 00:09:07.500 align:middle line:90%
Go, that's part of the process.

00:09:07.500 --> 00:09:09.840 align:middle line:84%
That's going to make me
smarter, wiser, better,

00:09:09.840 --> 00:09:12.450 align:middle line:84%
more kind, more
capable, more confident

00:09:12.450 --> 00:09:13.530 align:middle line:90%
to go through the muck.

00:09:13.530 --> 00:09:16.195 align:middle line:90%


00:09:16.195 --> 00:09:17.570 align:middle line:84%
I work with a lot
of Green Berets

00:09:17.570 --> 00:09:19.102 align:middle line:90%
and very elite military levels.

00:09:19.102 --> 00:09:20.810 align:middle line:84%
And they have this
great saying they say.

00:09:20.810 --> 00:09:24.272 align:middle line:90%
You have to embrace the suck.

00:09:24.272 --> 00:09:26.480 align:middle line:84%
You have to know, this is
going to suck a little bit.

00:09:26.480 --> 00:09:27.860 align:middle line:90%
All right, let's go at it, guys.

00:09:27.860 --> 00:09:29.210 align:middle line:90%
We know it's going to suck.

00:09:29.210 --> 00:09:34.100 align:middle line:84%
Just knowing that and allowing
that is really important.

00:09:34.100 --> 00:09:36.100 align:middle line:84%
And now, this person who
has a lot of potential,

00:09:36.100 --> 00:09:38.267 align:middle line:84%
a lot of greatness, who
could go to this next level,

00:09:38.267 --> 00:09:42.160 align:middle line:84%
they don't, because they're
not listening to that inside

00:09:42.160 --> 00:09:43.480 align:middle line:90%
restlessness.

00:09:43.480 --> 00:09:45.675 align:middle line:84%
That inside thing that
says, come on, man.

00:09:45.675 --> 00:09:47.800 align:middle line:84%
That inside thing that
says, we got to change this.

00:09:47.800 --> 00:09:50.520 align:middle line:84%
That inside thing that is scary
sometimes, because it says,

00:09:50.520 --> 00:09:54.010 align:middle line:84%
we got to blow all this up
because it's wrong for us.

00:09:54.010 --> 00:09:56.365 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, it feels
irresponsible to listen

00:09:56.365 --> 00:09:58.240 align:middle line:84%
to that voice, and very
responsible to listen

00:09:58.240 --> 00:10:00.130 align:middle line:84%
the person says,
now, be careful.

00:10:00.130 --> 00:10:02.290 align:middle line:84%
But if you're always
listening to that person

00:10:02.290 --> 00:10:08.020 align:middle line:84%
or that side of you, then what
ends up winning is certainty.

00:10:08.020 --> 00:10:11.350 align:middle line:84%
Because past the comfort
zone is a lot of unknown,

00:10:11.350 --> 00:10:12.835 align:middle line:90%
is a lot of fear.

00:10:12.835 --> 00:10:16.090 align:middle line:90%


00:10:16.090 --> 00:10:18.780 align:middle line:84%
And there's only three
psychological mechanisms

00:10:18.780 --> 00:10:19.920 align:middle line:90%
that create fear.

00:10:19.920 --> 00:10:22.480 align:middle line:90%
Number one is called loss pain.

00:10:22.480 --> 00:10:24.713 align:middle line:84%
Loss pain means, if
I do that, then I'm

00:10:24.713 --> 00:10:27.235 align:middle line:84%
going to lose something
I like over here.

00:10:27.235 --> 00:10:30.840 align:middle line:84%
If I go to change my diet,
then I lose the foods I love.

00:10:30.840 --> 00:10:34.200 align:middle line:84%
If I quit this job, then I lose
those co-workers I do like.

00:10:34.200 --> 00:10:35.790 align:middle line:90%
I lose my health insurance.

00:10:35.790 --> 00:10:36.840 align:middle line:84%
So people don't
change because they're

00:10:36.840 --> 00:10:38.465 align:middle line:84%
scared they're going
to lose something.

00:10:38.465 --> 00:10:41.700 align:middle line:84%
Lose something tangible,
lose something intangible.

00:10:41.700 --> 00:10:44.550 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes they feel like,
I'm going to lose respect.

00:10:44.550 --> 00:10:48.283 align:middle line:84%
And loss pain terrorizes
people, so they stay stuck.

00:10:48.283 --> 00:10:49.200 align:middle line:90%
Because you know what?

00:10:49.200 --> 00:10:50.500 align:middle line:90%
I know this.

00:10:50.500 --> 00:10:51.430 align:middle line:90%
I don't know that.

00:10:51.430 --> 00:10:53.400 align:middle line:84%
And I don't want to lose
the things I'm already

00:10:53.400 --> 00:10:54.655 align:middle line:90%
certain about in life.

00:10:54.655 --> 00:10:58.260 align:middle line:84%
A second thing that people
fear is called hardship pain.

00:10:58.260 --> 00:11:01.470 align:middle line:84%
The process of
changing will bring

00:11:01.470 --> 00:11:05.340 align:middle line:90%
doubt, uncertainty, discomfort.

00:11:05.340 --> 00:11:07.560 align:middle line:84%
It will bring
hardship to me, where

00:11:07.560 --> 00:11:10.860 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to stretch, and
learn, and retool new things.

00:11:10.860 --> 00:11:12.870 align:middle line:84%
People don't quit the
job because they go, ugh,

00:11:12.870 --> 00:11:14.310 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to have
to create a resume.

00:11:14.310 --> 00:11:15.350 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to have
to go interview.

00:11:15.350 --> 00:11:17.100 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to have to put
myself out there again.

00:11:17.100 --> 00:11:18.558 align:middle line:84%
People don't go
dating because they

00:11:18.558 --> 00:11:20.580 align:middle line:90%
say those same things today.

00:11:20.580 --> 00:11:22.920 align:middle line:84%
People don't go and try to
change because they say,

00:11:22.920 --> 00:11:24.720 align:middle line:84%
oh, if I want to
lose weight, I'm

00:11:24.720 --> 00:11:27.120 align:middle line:84%
going to have to learn
to cook new things.

00:11:27.120 --> 00:11:30.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to have to change my
schedule to go to the gym now.

00:11:30.730 --> 00:11:31.530 align:middle line:90%
It's going to hurt.

00:11:31.530 --> 00:11:33.180 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to be
sore all the time.

00:11:33.180 --> 00:11:34.410 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to do that.

00:11:34.410 --> 00:11:36.210 align:middle line:90%
That's process pain.

00:11:36.210 --> 00:11:39.270 align:middle line:84%
And then the last one
is called outcome pain.

00:11:39.270 --> 00:11:43.650 align:middle line:84%
Outcome pain is, I'm scared that
if I go through all of that, I

00:11:43.650 --> 00:11:48.120 align:middle line:84%
put myself out there, I
try, I endure the hardship,

00:11:48.120 --> 00:11:51.030 align:middle line:84%
the grass won't be
greener on the other side.

00:11:51.030 --> 00:11:54.060 align:middle line:84%
I tried all of this work,
I did all the things

00:11:54.060 --> 00:11:57.240 align:middle line:84%
you told me only
to be disappointed.

00:11:57.240 --> 00:11:59.520 align:middle line:84%
They're terrified
of disappointment.

00:11:59.520 --> 00:12:01.470 align:middle line:10%
It's psychological
warfare in their mind

00:12:01.470 --> 00:12:05.140 align:middle line:10%
going, if I do that, it
might not turn out well.

00:12:05.140 --> 00:12:06.170 align:middle line:10%
And then what happens?

00:12:06.170 --> 00:12:07.370 align:middle line:10%
Well, then I lose something.

00:12:07.370 --> 00:12:09.000 align:middle line:10%
What happens if
I lose something?

00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:10.650 align:middle line:90%
Then it becomes hard.

00:12:10.650 --> 00:12:13.110 align:middle line:84%
And they get trapped
in this spinning loop

00:12:13.110 --> 00:12:18.132 align:middle line:84%
of fear of loss, hardship, and
outcome that they didn't want.

00:12:18.132 --> 00:12:20.492 align:middle line:90%
[SOMBER MUSIC]

00:12:20.492 --> 00:12:21.440 align:middle line:90%


00:12:21.440 --> 00:12:25.460 align:middle line:10%
>> What helps mitigate
fear, and move fear away,

00:12:25.460 --> 00:12:27.650 align:middle line:10%
is often living on purpose.

00:12:27.650 --> 00:12:32.990 align:middle line:10%
You see, people who live on
purpose understand this rule--

00:12:32.990 --> 00:12:36.490 align:middle line:10%
that there is no good or
no bad that happens to you

00:12:36.490 --> 00:12:37.290 align:middle line:10%
in the world.

00:12:37.290 --> 00:12:39.230 align:middle line:90%
Nothing is good, nothing is bad.

00:12:39.230 --> 00:12:41.330 align:middle line:90%
Everything is just so.

00:12:41.330 --> 00:12:43.160 align:middle line:84%
The only question you
want to ask yourself

00:12:43.160 --> 00:12:45.440 align:middle line:84%
is, am I aligned
with my purpose?

00:12:45.440 --> 00:12:47.450 align:middle line:84%
Is what I'm doing
true to my purpose?

00:12:47.450 --> 00:12:51.470 align:middle line:84%
Now, the thing is, we
are not omniscient.

00:12:51.470 --> 00:12:53.810 align:middle line:84%
We don't know if any
action we are taking

00:12:53.810 --> 00:12:55.820 align:middle line:90%
is always the right action.

00:12:55.820 --> 00:12:57.960 align:middle line:84%
But the point is,
we take it anyway.

