00:19:57.130 --> 00:20:00.550 align:middle line:84%
from college, the only
job that really interested

00:20:00.550 --> 00:20:02.080 align:middle line:84%
me was something
that was active,

00:20:02.080 --> 00:20:04.790 align:middle line:84%
so I got myself a job on the
floor of the New York Stock

00:20:04.790 --> 00:20:07.470 align:middle line:90%
Exchange.

00:20:07.470 --> 00:20:09.630 align:middle line:84%
So you're standing all
day long, and people

00:20:09.630 --> 00:20:13.200 align:middle line:84%
are screaming and yelling, and
it's a very exciting, energetic

00:20:13.200 --> 00:20:15.120 align:middle line:90%
place to work.

00:20:15.120 --> 00:20:17.040 align:middle line:84%
Everyone was making
millions of dollars,

00:20:17.040 --> 00:20:19.380 align:middle line:84%
but while they were
rich financially,

00:20:19.380 --> 00:20:22.910 align:middle line:90%
they were spiritually bankrupt.

00:20:22.910 --> 00:20:25.730 align:middle line:84%
And I started hearing this
small voice inside that said,

00:20:25.730 --> 00:20:28.040 align:middle line:84%
this isn't what
you're supposed to do.

00:20:28.040 --> 00:20:29.870 align:middle line:84%
This is not where
you're supposed to be.

00:20:29.870 --> 00:20:34.490 align:middle line:84%
And I tried to silence that
voice because I had debt.

00:20:34.490 --> 00:20:37.740 align:middle line:84%
Feeling like I should
be doing something else,

00:20:37.740 --> 00:20:39.460 align:middle line:84%
but I didn't know
what that was was

00:20:39.460 --> 00:20:41.460 align:middle line:84%
creating a lot of stress
and anxiety in my life.

00:20:41.460 --> 00:20:44.085 align:middle line:84%
And one day, I was on the floor
of the New York Stock Exchange,

00:20:44.085 --> 00:20:46.730 align:middle line:84%
and I started getting
a panic attack.

00:20:46.730 --> 00:20:48.590 align:middle line:84%
I remember telling
my boss at the time,

00:20:48.590 --> 00:20:51.620 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to go run out
and get a cup of coffee.

00:20:51.620 --> 00:20:54.800 align:middle line:84%
And I left the floor, and
instead of going to get coffee,

00:20:54.800 --> 00:20:56.300 align:middle line:90%
I ran to a church.

00:20:56.300 --> 00:20:59.810 align:middle line:84%
And I sat myself down on
the steps of Trinity Church,

00:20:59.810 --> 00:21:02.480 align:middle line:84%
outside the exchange, and
I just started crying,

00:21:02.480 --> 00:21:05.470 align:middle line:84%
because I didn't
know what else to do.

00:21:05.470 --> 00:21:10.710 align:middle line:84%
I felt all of this pressure,
and fear, and uncertainty,

00:21:10.710 --> 00:21:13.110 align:middle line:84%
and self-doubt, thinking
like, I have this job.

00:21:13.110 --> 00:21:14.500 align:middle line:90%
I'm getting a steady paycheck.

00:21:14.500 --> 00:21:16.830 align:middle line:84%
I should be so grateful
to have this position,

00:21:16.830 --> 00:21:18.195 align:middle line:90%
and all I want to do is quit.

00:21:18.195 --> 00:21:20.820 align:middle line:84%
And I thought I was going to be
a disappointment to my parents,

00:21:20.820 --> 00:21:22.740 align:middle line:84%
and to my friends,
and to everyone.

00:21:22.740 --> 00:21:24.630 align:middle line:84%
And I remember calling
my dad on a cell phone

00:21:24.630 --> 00:21:26.820 align:middle line:84%
and just bawling my
eyes out and saying,

00:21:26.820 --> 00:21:28.320 align:middle line:84%
Dad, I don't want
to disappoint you,

00:21:28.320 --> 00:21:29.800 align:middle line:90%
but I can't do this anymore.

00:21:29.800 --> 00:21:31.633 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know what
the hell I want to do,

00:21:31.633 --> 00:21:33.610 align:middle line:90%
but I gotta do something else.

00:21:33.610 --> 00:21:36.970 align:middle line:84%
And he said something to me
that forever changed my life.

00:21:36.970 --> 00:21:40.890 align:middle line:84%
And he said, Rie, you've worked
since you were nine years old.

00:21:40.890 --> 00:21:43.110 align:middle line:84%
You started babysitting,
and selling ice cream,

00:21:43.110 --> 00:21:45.235 align:middle line:84%
and working at the beach,
and you've always worked.

00:21:45.235 --> 00:21:47.760 align:middle line:84%
He's like, I'm not worrying
about you paying your bills.

00:21:47.760 --> 00:21:51.390 align:middle line:84%
He goes, but you have to
find something that you love.

00:21:51.390 --> 00:21:53.250 align:middle line:84%
Because once you
find that, it's never

00:21:53.250 --> 00:21:55.000 align:middle line:90%
going to feel like work again.

00:21:55.000 --> 00:21:58.380 align:middle line:84%
So as long as it takes you to
try every different thing you

00:21:58.380 --> 00:22:00.780 align:middle line:84%
could possibly imagine,
you have to keep

00:22:00.780 --> 00:22:02.820 align:middle line:90%
searching until you find it.

00:22:02.820 --> 00:22:05.610 align:middle line:84%
So if you need to quit, I'm
not going to be disappointed.

00:22:05.610 --> 00:22:07.380 align:middle line:84%
But you have to do
this, and you have

00:22:07.380 --> 00:22:09.040 align:middle line:90%
to find something you love.

00:22:09.040 --> 00:22:11.010 align:middle line:84%
And when I hung up
for my dad, I remember

00:22:11.010 --> 00:22:12.900 align:middle line:84%
within like the next
week, I quit my job,

00:22:12.900 --> 00:22:14.848 align:middle line:84%
and I went on an
odyssey to find what

00:22:14.848 --> 00:22:16.140 align:middle line:90%
I was meant to do in the world.

00:22:16.140 --> 00:22:21.750 align:middle line:90%


00:22:21.750 --> 00:22:25.230 align:middle line:10%
My first step was really
doing a bit of an excavation

00:22:25.230 --> 00:22:28.230 align:middle line:10%
and asking myself, what
am I really interested in?

00:22:28.230 --> 00:22:29.700 align:middle line:90%
What have I always been good at?

00:22:29.700 --> 00:22:31.440 align:middle line:90%
What sounds exciting to me?

00:22:31.440 --> 00:22:34.110 align:middle line:84%
Because again, I felt
paralyzed, because the thing

00:22:34.110 --> 00:22:36.930 align:middle line:84%
that I had just spent four
years studying, the epitome

00:22:36.930 --> 00:22:38.460 align:middle line:90%
of the job, that wasn't it.

00:22:38.460 --> 00:22:41.670 align:middle line:84%
So looking inside, I
really had two clues.

00:22:41.670 --> 00:22:44.160 align:middle line:84%
One was that I was
very interested

00:22:44.160 --> 00:22:45.240 align:middle line:90%
in the world of business.

00:22:45.240 --> 00:22:46.690 align:middle line:84%
My dad was a small
business owner,

00:22:46.690 --> 00:22:49.080 align:middle line:84%
so I understood what that
was like growing up with him.

00:22:49.080 --> 00:22:51.090 align:middle line:84%
And the other was
art and creativity.

00:22:51.090 --> 00:22:53.490 align:middle line:84%
I had always drawn,
and done fine art,

00:22:53.490 --> 00:22:55.440 align:middle line:84%
and considered being
an animator for Disney,

00:22:55.440 --> 00:22:56.405 align:middle line:90%
or a fashion designer.

00:22:56.405 --> 00:22:57.780 align:middle line:84%
So I was like,
OK, well, how do I

00:22:57.780 --> 00:23:01.110 align:middle line:84%
mesh these two passions
around business,

00:23:01.110 --> 00:23:03.750 align:middle line:84%
and small business, and
something around making money,

00:23:03.750 --> 00:23:05.430 align:middle line:90%
but also, it has to be creative.

00:23:05.430 --> 00:23:09.550 align:middle line:84%
And the idea that came to
me was magazine publishing.

00:23:09.550 --> 00:23:13.690 align:middle line:10%
And I got into the ad sales
department of a magazine called

00:23:13.690 --> 00:23:15.880 align:middle line:10%
"Gourmet," which was
part of Condé Nast,

00:23:15.880 --> 00:23:18.470 align:middle line:10%
that very big magazine
publishing company.

00:23:18.470 --> 00:23:20.512 align:middle line:84%
And I remember starting
and being so excited.

00:23:20.512 --> 00:23:21.970 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, oh, this
has gotta be it.

00:23:21.970 --> 00:23:24.220 align:middle line:84%
And I was thrilled to be
able to learn the business.

00:23:24.220 --> 00:23:26.590 align:middle line:84%
I had a great boss, and
I had a great publisher,

00:23:26.590 --> 00:23:29.020 align:middle line:84%
and they were just these
powerful, strong, intelligent

00:23:29.020 --> 00:23:29.820 align:middle line:90%
women.

00:23:29.820 --> 00:23:31.600 align:middle line:84%
But about six
months in, I started

00:23:31.600 --> 00:23:34.210 align:middle line:84%
hearing that voice again that
said, Marie, this isn't it.

00:23:34.210 --> 00:23:35.920 align:middle line:90%
And I was like, oh, no.

00:23:35.920 --> 00:23:37.210 align:middle line:90%
Not this again.

00:23:37.210 --> 00:23:38.260 align:middle line:90%
No, not this again.

00:23:38.260 --> 00:23:40.400 align:middle line:84%
I was like, wait,
this has to be it.

00:23:40.400 --> 00:23:42.010 align:middle line:84%
And at this point,
I have to tell you,

00:23:42.010 --> 00:23:44.410 align:middle line:84%
I really started to
feel a sense of panic.

00:23:44.410 --> 00:23:46.180 align:middle line:90%
I started to feel broken.

00:23:46.180 --> 00:23:48.650 align:middle line:84%
I knew I had a ton
of potential in me.

00:23:48.650 --> 00:23:50.020 align:middle line:90%
I knew I was a hard worker.

00:23:50.020 --> 00:23:53.170 align:middle line:84%
I knew I wanted to
contribute to the world.

00:23:53.170 --> 00:23:56.530 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't seem to fit
in to the regular corporate

00:23:56.530 --> 00:23:57.370 align:middle line:90%
structure.

00:23:57.370 --> 00:23:58.828 align:middle line:84%
So one day, I was
on the internet--

00:23:58.828 --> 00:24:00.470 align:middle line:84%
probably when I
shouldn't have been--

00:24:00.470 --> 00:24:03.910 align:middle line:84%
and I stumbled upon this
article about a new profession

00:24:03.910 --> 00:24:05.980 align:middle line:90%
at the time called coaching.

00:24:05.980 --> 00:24:07.880 align:middle line:90%
Now, this is back in 1999.

00:24:07.880 --> 00:24:11.930 align:middle line:84%
This is well before coaching
was anything in the mainstream.

00:24:11.930 --> 00:24:14.230 align:middle line:84%
And I remember
reading this article,

00:24:14.230 --> 00:24:17.470 align:middle line:84%
and something in my heart lit
up like nothing ever before.

00:24:17.470 --> 00:24:19.420 align:middle line:84%
It really was one of
those moments where

00:24:19.420 --> 00:24:22.450 align:middle line:84%
it feels like the clouds parted,
and the angels were singing,

00:24:22.450 --> 00:24:24.790 align:middle line:84%
and sunbeams were
just shooting down.

00:24:24.790 --> 00:24:28.390 align:middle line:84%
And something in my soul,
something in my being

00:24:28.390 --> 00:24:30.700 align:middle line:90%
felt like this was right.

00:24:30.700 --> 00:24:32.710 align:middle line:84%
This was something
that was more exciting.

00:24:32.710 --> 00:24:34.180 align:middle line:90%
There was something aligned.

00:24:34.180 --> 00:24:37.670 align:middle line:84%
I had to pursue it, even
though it didn't make sense.

00:24:37.670 --> 00:24:40.810 align:middle line:84%
So I signed up for a three-year
coach training program,

00:24:40.810 --> 00:24:43.210 align:middle line:84%
and I started to do my
studies at night while I kept

00:24:43.210 --> 00:24:46.920 align:middle line:90%
my magazine job during the day.

00:24:46.920 --> 00:24:49.440 align:middle line:84%
A few months in, I get a
call from the HR department.

00:24:49.440 --> 00:24:52.950 align:middle line:84%
They wanted to offer me a
promotion at "Vogue" magazine.

00:24:52.950 --> 00:24:54.930 align:middle line:90%
This was my fork in the road.

00:24:54.930 --> 00:24:56.640 align:middle line:84%
Do you take this
promotion, which

00:24:56.640 --> 00:25:00.480 align:middle line:84%
is more money, and more
prestige, a steady paycheck,

00:25:00.480 --> 00:25:01.745 align:middle line:90%
health benefits--

00:25:01.745 --> 00:25:03.120 align:middle line:84%
all of the things
that one should

00:25:03.120 --> 00:25:05.610 align:middle line:84%
want when you're getting
started in your career--

00:25:05.610 --> 00:25:08.190 align:middle line:84%
or do you quit and
do this weird thing

00:25:08.190 --> 00:25:10.133 align:middle line:84%
that no one has ever
heard of called coaching

00:25:10.133 --> 00:25:11.550 align:middle line:84%
and start your own
business, which

00:25:11.550 --> 00:25:13.440 align:middle line:84%
you have no idea how
to do, and you're

00:25:13.440 --> 00:25:15.600 align:middle line:84%
carrying thousands and
thousands of dollars of debt

00:25:15.600 --> 00:25:18.690 align:middle line:84%
from college, and you have
to take care of yourself.

00:25:18.690 --> 00:25:20.010 align:middle line:90%
So of course, I quit.

00:25:20.010 --> 00:25:21.180 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLES]

00:25:21.180 --> 00:25:23.820 align:middle line:84%
And I started bartending,
and waiting tables, and doing

00:25:23.820 --> 00:25:25.900 align:middle line:90%
every odd job I possibly could.

00:25:25.900 --> 00:25:28.680 align:middle line:84%
And I started working on
my business during the day,

00:25:28.680 --> 00:25:31.530 align:middle line:84%
and just hustling my buns
off on nights and weekends

00:25:31.530 --> 00:25:33.300 align:middle line:90%
to fund this brand new business.

00:25:33.300 --> 00:25:38.180 align:middle line:90%


00:25:38.180 --> 00:25:41.120 align:middle line:90%
[LIGHT MUSIC]

00:25:41.120 --> 00:25:44.930 align:middle line:84%
So over the years, I recognized
that one of my greatest

00:25:44.930 --> 00:25:47.690 align:middle line:84%
abilities was to be able
to communicate with people.

00:25:47.690 --> 00:25:49.370 align:middle line:90%
I love teaching on video.

00:25:49.370 --> 00:25:51.603 align:middle line:84%
I had a part of my career
in health and fitness

00:25:51.603 --> 00:25:54.020 align:middle line:84%
where I was teaching hip hop,
and I was a Nike Elite dance

00:25:54.020 --> 00:25:55.850 align:middle line:84%
athlete, and I was creating
all these fitness videos.

00:25:55.850 --> 00:25:57.080 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
things that I loved

00:25:57.080 --> 00:25:59.000 align:middle line:84%
about that was just being able
to talk to people straight

00:25:59.000 --> 00:26:00.740 align:middle line:84%
to camera and show
them how to do things,

00:26:00.740 --> 00:26:03.560 align:middle line:84%
and have them go from
feeling insecure and afraid

00:26:03.560 --> 00:26:06.660 align:middle line:84%
and a lot of self-doubt to
this other place of like,

00:26:06.660 --> 00:26:08.615 align:middle line:90%
oh my goodness, I can do this.

00:26:08.615 --> 00:26:10.490 align:middle line:84%
And I feel like that's
one of my superpowers.

00:26:10.490 --> 00:26:13.310 align:middle line:84%
That helps people
really take what

00:26:13.310 --> 00:26:15.530 align:middle line:84%
it is that they want
to do in this world

00:26:15.530 --> 00:26:16.730 align:middle line:90%
and bring it to life.

00:26:16.730 --> 00:26:18.470 align:middle line:84%
If there's a change they
want to make in their health,

00:26:18.470 --> 00:26:20.570 align:middle line:84%
or in their relationships,
or in their financial life,

00:26:20.570 --> 00:26:22.280 align:middle line:84%
or in their mental
or emotional health,

00:26:22.280 --> 00:26:24.380 align:middle line:84%
or they want to take this
idea they have for a business

00:26:24.380 --> 00:26:26.047 align:middle line:84%
and grow it, or their
existing business,

00:26:26.047 --> 00:26:28.490 align:middle line:84%
and take it to new
heights, a lot of it

00:26:28.490 --> 00:26:31.100 align:middle line:84%
comes from really simple
tools and the application

00:26:31.100 --> 00:26:32.900 align:middle line:90%
of those tools consistently.

00:26:32.900 --> 00:26:37.302 align:middle line:84%
And so many of us don't have
voices of encouragement.

00:26:37.302 --> 00:26:40.400 align:middle line:90%


00:26:40.400 --> 00:26:43.670 align:middle line:84%
So I think when any of
us are feeling lost,

00:26:43.670 --> 00:26:46.010 align:middle line:84%
or feeling stuck,
or feeling like,

00:26:46.010 --> 00:26:47.930 align:middle line:84%
gosh, nothing's
working right now,

00:26:47.930 --> 00:26:49.730 align:middle line:84%
I think one of the
best things we can do--

00:26:49.730 --> 00:26:53.190 align:middle line:84%
and it's so counter-intuitive--
is we have to celebrate.

00:26:53.190 --> 00:26:56.130 align:middle line:84%
We have to celebrate the fact
that we're in a tough spot.

00:26:56.130 --> 00:26:56.930 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:26:56.930 --> 00:26:59.660 align:middle line:84%
Because we're about to have
some kind of breakthrough.

00:26:59.660 --> 00:27:01.340 align:middle line:84%
Something in our
life is not working,

00:27:01.340 --> 00:27:02.600 align:middle line:84%
and we've gotten
ourselves to the point

00:27:02.600 --> 00:27:04.040 align:middle line:84%
that we're willing
to take action

00:27:04.040 --> 00:27:05.870 align:middle line:84%
to do something about it,
so that means change is

00:27:05.870 --> 00:27:06.470 align:middle line:90%
on the horizon.

00:27:06.470 --> 00:27:08.512 align:middle line:84%
So again, I know it's a
little counter-intuitive,

00:27:08.512 --> 00:27:10.137 align:middle line:84%
but please, take a
minute to celebrate,

00:27:10.137 --> 00:27:12.095 align:middle line:84%
because something's
off-track, and you're going

00:27:12.095 --> 00:27:13.560 align:middle line:90%
to get it right back on track.

00:27:13.560 --> 00:27:16.190 align:middle line:84%
The next thing we got to
do is start where we are.

00:27:16.190 --> 00:27:18.625 align:middle line:84%
Oftentimes, we think we
have to change everything.

00:27:18.625 --> 00:27:20.750 align:middle line:84%
But really, what we have
to change is our attitude,

00:27:20.750 --> 00:27:21.890 align:middle line:90%
and how we're showing up.

00:27:21.890 --> 00:27:24.620 align:middle line:84%
So can you start with
the little things?

00:27:24.620 --> 00:27:26.390 align:middle line:84%
In the morning, can
you make your bed

00:27:26.390 --> 00:27:27.800 align:middle line:90%
with enthusiasm and passion?

00:27:27.800 --> 00:27:30.560 align:middle line:84%
Can you be the best
damn bed-maker ever?

00:27:30.560 --> 00:27:32.690 align:middle line:84%
Can you brush your teeth
like you really mean it?

00:27:32.690 --> 00:27:34.610 align:middle line:84%
Can you start talking
with your family

00:27:34.610 --> 00:27:36.200 align:middle line:84%
like they're the
best family ever?

00:27:36.200 --> 00:27:38.450 align:middle line:84%
Can you show up at
work and actually

00:27:38.450 --> 00:27:41.870 align:middle line:84%
give your excellence, and your
best, and your heart and soul?

00:27:41.870 --> 00:27:43.670 align:middle line:84%
Can you go into
that grocery store,

00:27:43.670 --> 00:27:45.650 align:middle line:84%
can you put a smile
on somebody's face?

00:27:45.650 --> 00:27:48.800 align:middle line:84%
I know these things may
sound trite or insignificant,

00:27:48.800 --> 00:27:49.940 align:middle line:90%
but they're not.

00:27:49.940 --> 00:27:52.920 align:middle line:84%
Because you can't be miserable
throughout your whole day.

00:27:52.920 --> 00:27:55.060 align:middle line:84%
80%, 90% of your
day complaining,

00:27:55.060 --> 00:27:57.380 align:middle line:84%
stuck, nothing's
working, and then expect

00:27:57.380 --> 00:27:58.850 align:middle line:90%
to have some big breakthrough.

00:27:58.850 --> 00:28:01.070 align:middle line:84%
